Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash
and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if
necessary.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @Asparagus{6%ounce}.

> Save potatoes for another use.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon} and
a pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Skip this step for asparagus!

Add @Butter{1%tablespoon} to a small #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until
melted, ~{30-45%seconds}. Stir in @Panko Breadcrumbs{½%cup}, @Mozzarella Cheese{½%cup},
a drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt
and pepper. Place on a second lightly oiled baking sheet. Brush tops of chicken
with a thin layer of @Pesto{4%tablespoon} (you may not use all the pesto).
Mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast on middle rack until chicken is browned and cooked through,
~{20-22%minutes}.

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Push
potatoes to one side of sheet. Carefully toss green beans on opposite side of
sheet with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until potatoes and green beans are browned and tender,
~{12-15%minutes}.

Toss green beans on one side of sheet as instructed; on empty side of sheet,
toss asparagus with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack
for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Divide potatoes, chicken, and green beans between plates. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.